                                    CSS
        
                - Cascading Style sheet

            CSS is a key value pair of properties:

            key: value,
            key: value,
            key: value,

            key represents property of the CSS and value is value of the CSS property.

            ex:

            font-size: 20px;


        CSS can be added in three different ways in the document.

        - inline CSS
        - internal CSS
        - external CSS

    1) Inline CSS
        - it gets added directly inside the tag of the HTML with style attribute.

    2) Internal CSS
        - is used to write CSS within the same HTML document using <style></style>.

        here,
            we need to use CSS Selectors to provide to which element the css should gets applied.

        i) Using Tag Name:
            <style>
                div{

                }
            </style>

            here, div is a selector by tag name.
        
        ii) Using Class:
            - in html tag give class as a attribute ex: class="para" then in css
                .para{

                }
            here (.) represents that it is a class.
        
        iii) Using Id:
            - this is generally used to apply some styles to only one element in HTML Document.
                #big-text{
                    // styles
                }

    3) External CSS
        - Here we create seperate file the extention is .css
        - then include that file in HTML to apply that CSS.




        CSS Color:

    1) by using color name:
        around 140 colors
    
    2) using hexadecimal code:

        #000000

        16*16*16*16*16*16

        RGB

    3) using rgb function:

        rgb(0-255,0-255,0-255);

    4) using hsl function:

        hsl(0-360, 0-100%, 0,100%);


